.TH "ata_eh_acquire" 9 "ata_eh_acquire" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ata_eh_acquire \- acquire EH ownership
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ata_eh_acquire
.BI "(struct ata_port *ap "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ap" 12
ATA port to acquire EH ownership for

Acquire EH ownership for \fIap\fP.  This is the basic exclusion
mechanism for ports sharing a host.  Only one port hanging off
the same host can claim the ownership of EH.

LOCKING:
EH context.
